second net, which learns to check quality of language (DONE).  Maybe at first train it by feeding it good language, so it knows what should get good ratings; it could also assume that user input should have a positive rating (maybe say +8 for user input) (DONE).  It can also compare its ratings of Virgil's output to the user-supplied ratings (DONE).  Eventually, it will be able to rate Virgil automatically, and then we can set up Virgil as an autonomous thing, conversing without having to ask for ratings.

What are the nodetypes?
SWITCH - cleared every input; local to each conn
SESSION - local to each conn
GLOBAL - shared over all conns; state saved between runs
